1.Bar plot of the mean total crashes by "abbrev"¶

In [6]:
sns.barplot(x="abbrev", y="total", data=dataset)
plt.xlabel("Abbreviation")
plt.ylabel("Mean Total Crashes")
plt.title("Bar Plot: Mean Total Crashes by Abbreviation")
plt.show()
In [12]:
#Inference- This bar plot displays the mean total crashes for each "abbrev".It can help identify which states, on average, have higher or lower total crashes.

In [9]:
sns.histplot(dataset["total"], bins=15, kde=True)

plt.title("Histogram of Total Crashes")
plt.show()
In [10]:
#Inference- The histogram shows the distribution of the "total" column, which represents the total number of crashes. It appears that the majority of observations have a lower total number of crashes, with a right-skewed distribution.
